"title": "2309: Jesus Christ, as judge",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2309",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ executed judgment against the forces of evil through his death on the cross. Individuals will be judged according to their response to his saving grace.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ is appointed judge by God the Father</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:22\">JHN 5:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:27\">JHN 5:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:42\">ACT 10:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:31\">ACT 17:31</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ is a just judge</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:30\">JHN 5:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:3-Isa11:4\">ISA 11:3–11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:3\">MIC 4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:15-John8:16\">JHN 8:15–8:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:31\">ACT 17:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:11\">REV 19:11</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's death brought judgment on Satan and evil world powers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:31-John12:33\">JHN 12:31–12:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:11\">JHN 16:11</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ will act as judge at the end of time</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:1\">2TI 4:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:31-Matt25:32\">MAT 25:31–25:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:16\">ROM 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:7-2Thess1:10\">2TH 1:7–1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:8\">2TI 4:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:11-Rev19:16\">REV 19:11–19:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:12\">REV 22:12</a></p>\n<h2>People will be judged according to their response to Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:18\">JHN 3:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:32-Matt10:33\">MAT 10:32–10:33</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:8-Luke12:9\">LUK 12:8–12:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:38\">MRK 8:38</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:26\">LUK 9:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:39\">JHN 9:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:48\">JHN 12:48</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's teaching on judgment</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ will separate the righteous from the unrighteous</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:31-Matt25:32\">MAT 25:31–25:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:12\">MAT 3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:24-Matt13:30\">MAT 13:24–13:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:36-Matt13:42\">MAT 13:36–13:42</a> <em>the parable of the weeds</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:47-Matt13:50\">MAT 13:47–13:50</a> <em>the parable of the net</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:33-Matt25:46\">MAT 25:33–25:46</a> <em>the parable of the sheep and the goats</em></p>\n<h3>Those who reject Jesus Christ will be punished</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:34-Dan2:35\">DAN 2:34–2:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:33-Matt21:44\">MAT 21:33–21:44</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:1-Mark12:11\">MRK 12:1–12:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:9-Luke20:18\">LUK 20:9–20:18</a> <em>the parable of the tenants</em></p>\n<h3>Christians will stand before Jesus Christ as judge and be rewarded for what they have done</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:27\">MAT 16:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:14-Matt25:30\">MAT 25:14–25:30</a> <em>the parable of the talents</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:12-Luke19:27\">LUK 19:12–19:27</a> <em>the parable of the ten minas</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:10\">2CO 5:10</a></p>\n<h3>The day of Jesus Christ's return as judge is unknown</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:32-Mark13:36\">MRK 13:32–13:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:36-Matt24:44\">MAT 24:36–24:44</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:26-Luke17:37\">LUK 17:26–17:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:1-Matt25:13\">MAT 25:1–25:13</a> <em>the parable of the ten virgins</em></p>",
